# Testing Rules

## Purpose
80%+ coverage on critical modules; prevent tenant leaks and regressions.

## Requirements
- Jest unit tests for services; mock repositories.
- Integration tests with testcontainers (Postgres, Redis) for API + repos.
- Playwright E2E: login, create property, inquiry pipeline, billing smoke.
- Every new repository method: tenant isolation negative test.
- Every new endpoint: RBAC forbidden test for unauthorized role.
- CI blocks merge on test failure.

## Restrictions
- No tests that depend on production DB.
- No skipped tests without ticket reference.
- No asserting implementation details over behavior.

## Best Practices
- Factory helpers for org, user, property, inquiry fixtures.
- Snapshot tests only for stable DTO serializers.
- Name tests: `should reject cross-tenant access when...`

## Anti-Patterns
- Testing controllers without guards enabled.
- 100% coverage on trivial getters with zero business tests.

## Examples

```typescript
it('should return 404 when inquiry belongs to other tenant', async () => {
  const other = await createInquiry(otherTenant);
  await expect(service.find(other.id, myTenantCtx)).rejects.toBeNotFound();
});
```
